.TH DAHUGEPAGES 1 "2025-12-29" "dumbass-tree" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dahugepages \- dumbass-friendly hugepages helper (Linux)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dahugepages
[\-\-dry-run] [\-\-verbose]
.I <command>
[\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
dahugepages inspects and configures Linux hugepages (hugetlb) and THP.
It reads /proc/meminfo and /sys and shells out to mount(8) when needed.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B dahugepages status
Show hugepage + THP status.
.TP
.B dahugepages alloc \-\-size 2M|1G \-\-count N
Reserve hugepages of a given size (requires root).
.TP
.B dahugepages free \-\-size 2M|1G
Free reserved hugepages (set count to 0, requires root).
.TP
.B dahugepages mount \fImountpoint\fR [\-\-size 2M|1G] [\-\-mode OCTAL] [\-\-gid GID]
Mount hugetlbfs (requires root).
.TP
.B dahugepages thp
Print THP mode.
.TP
.B dahugepages thp \-\-set always|madvise|never
Set THP mode (requires root).
.TP
.B dahugepages persist ...
Print example sysctl and fstab lines for persistence.
.SH SEE ALSO
Documentation in dumbass-tree/docs/hugepages-for-dummies.md.
